90, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From the Latin form of the Greek name <i>Alexandros</i>, from <i>alexein</i> ‘to defend’ + <i>anēr</i> ‘man, warrior’ (genitive <i>andros</i>). The name became extremely popular in the post-classical period, and was borne by several individuals in the New Testament and some early Christian saints. Its use as a common given name throughout Europe, however, derives largely from the fame of  Alexander the Great , King of Macedon (  356–323  bc  ), around whom a large body of popular legend grew up in late antiquity, much of which came to be embodied in the medieval ‘Alexander romances’."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs. Alexander Wilsone was born about 1574, in Scotland, United Kingdom. She married Alexander Wilsone about 1592, in Scotland, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 4 sons and 6 daughters."},"et":{"about 1574–":"umbes 1574–Surnud","1574–Male":"1574–Surnud","1590–1650":"1590–1650","1592–Female":"1592–Surnud","1595–Female":"1595–Surnud","1597–Female":"1597–Surnud","1598–Female":"1598–Surnud","1600–Male":"1600–Surnud","1605–Male":"1605–Surnud","1607–Male":"1607–Surnud","1614–Male":"1614–Surnud","1616–Female":"1616–Surnud","1574–Female":"1574–Surnud","1592":"1592","1590":"1590","1600":"1600","1598":"1598","1597":"1597","1574":"1574","1595":"1595","1650":"1650","about 1574":"umbes 1574","1607":"1607","1605":"1605","1616":"1616","about 1592":"umbes 1592","1614":"1614","Dunbar, East Lothian, Scotland":"Dunbar, Haddingtonshire, Scotland","Perthshire, Scotland":"Perthshire, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Scotland":"Šotimaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1574–":"noin 1574–Kuollut","1574–Male":"1574–Kuollut","1590–1650":"1590–1650","1592–Female":"1592–Kuollut","1595–Female":"1595–Kuollut","1597–Female":"1597–Kuollut","1598–Female":"1598–Kuollut","1600–Male":"1600–Kuollut","1605–Male":"1605–Kuollut","1607–Male":"1607–Kuollut","1614–Male":"1614–Kuollut","1616–Female":"1616–Kuollut","1574–Female":"1574–Kuollut","1592":"1592","1590